history.content:
We are conducting a user study on interactive data visualization use — it will be a series of web-based tasks to analyze a data set using the tool provided. The study is in person (in BiD lab in hearst mining building), and it will take around 30 minutes. You will be compensated $10 Amazon credit. This study is approved by the Berkeley IRB.

If you are interested in playing with some data analysis tools, making some quick money, and contributing to research, send Yifan an email at yifanwu@berkeley.edu (with the title "december data vis study"). Thanks.
history.subject: Participate in User Study! ($10 Amazon Credit)
